==English==

===Etymology===
A reference to [[w:Book of Hosea|Hosea]] [[s:Bible (King James)/Hosea#Chapter 8|8:7]]

===Proverb===
'''[[sow|Sow]] [[the]] [[wind]], [[reap]] [[the]] [[whirlwind]].'''

# Every decision has consequences; a person's actions will come back to him.

====Synonyms====
* [[there's no such thing as a free lunch]].
** also [[TANSTAAFL]], [[TINSTAAFL]]
* [[what goes around, comes around]].
* [[get out what one puts in]].
* [[get what one pays for]].
* [[reap what one sows]].

